[[File:Bataille_Waterloo_1815_reconstitution_2011_cuirassier.jpg|thumb|2011]] [[File:Bataille Waterloo 1815 reconstitution 2011 3.jpg|thumb|In the 2011 recreation, footsoldiers fire guns]] The '''Battle of Waterloo reenactment''' is an annual modern recreation of the 19th century [[Battle of Waterloo]] on the original battlefield in [[Waterloo, Belgium]].
It is held every June on the weekend nearest to the historic date of the Battle of Waterloo (18 June 1815). In a regular year there will be 600–800 reenactors. The 5-year-anniversaries are greater events with 1,500–2,000 reenactors from France, Belgium, The Netherlands, Great Britain, Germany, Poland and Russia.
{| |[[File:Bataille Waterloo 1815 reconstitution 2011 2.jpg|thumbnail|left|500px|French cavalry, June 2011]] |}
==Waterloo 2015== A major event, one of the largest ever staged, was held on the site of the battle to mark the 200th anniversary of the engagement. 6,200 re-enactors, 330 horses, and 120 cannons<ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/battle-of-waterloo/11688355/Battle-of-Waterloo-relived-the-sound-a-fury-of-a-Napoleonic-war-re-enactment.html Battle of Waterloo relived: the sound a fury of a Napoleonic war re-enactment, The Telegraph]</ref> took part in actions in an arena area close to [[La Haye Sainte]]. During the event, the Allied Army was camped at [[Hougoumont]],<ref>[http://montys-caravan.blogspot.co.uk/2015/06/waterloo-2015-part-1-allied-camp.html?showComment=1435052438970 Photos of the Allied camp]</ref> with the French camped about a mile away from [[La Caillou]].<ref>[http://montys-caravan.blogspot.co.uk/2015/06/waterloo-2015-part-2-french-camp.html Photos of the French camp]</ref>
The event was opened with a poetic interpretation of the Battle, created by [[Luc Petit]].<ref>[http://inferno2015.prezly.com/inferno-a-poetic-interpretation-of-the-battle-of-waterloo-in-twelve-tableaux-in-which-the-imagination-plays-a-central-role# Inferno] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626122329/http://inferno2015.prezly.com/inferno-a-poetic-interpretation-of-the-battle-of-waterloo-in-twelve-tableaux-in-which-the-imagination-plays-a-central-role |date=2015-06-26 }}</ref> The show was located on a stage 150 metres long, with giant projector screens, pyrotechnics, dancers, classical musicians and local choirs – in addition to cast members drawn from the re-enactment groups.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/huge-sound-light-show-waterloo-bicentenary-204947748.html Huge sound-and-light show for Waterloo bicentenary, AFP/Yahoo News]</ref> Three re-enactors were injured by explosives during this production, with one being taken to hospital with serious burns.<ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/battle-of-waterloo/11686533/Portable-loos-and-Belgian-officiousness-When-war-breaks-out-at-the-Battle-of-Waterloo-2015.html Portable loos and Belgian officiousness: When 'war' breaks out at the Battle of Waterloo, 2015, The Telegraph]</ref>
