{{Politics of Uzbekistan}}
An '''[[independence referendum]]''' was held in the [[Uzbekistan|Republic of Uzbekistan]] on 29 December 1991,<ref>[[Dieter Nohlen]], Florian Grotz & Christof Hartmann (2001) ''Elections in Asia: A data handbook, Volume I'', p490 {{ISBN|0-19-924958-X}}</ref> alongside [[Uzbekistani presidential election, 1991|presidential elections]]. The result was 98.3% of voters in favour, with a turnout of 94.1%.<ref>Nohlen et al, p492</ref>
==Background== In a [[Soviet Union referendum, 1991|USSR-wide referendum]] held in March, 95% of voters in the [[Uzbek Soviet Socialist Republic|Uzbek SSR]] voted in favour of preserving the [[Soviet Union]] as "a renewed federation of equal sovereign republics in which the rights and freedom of an individual of any nationality will be fully guaranteed?". There was also a separate question asked only in the Uzbek SSR, with 95% of voters voting in favour of the proposal that the country "should remain part of a renewed Union (federation) as a sovereign republic with equal rights".<ref>[http://www.sudd.ch/event.php?lang=en&id=uz011991 Uzbekistan, 17 March 1991: Equal sovereign republic] Direct Democracy {{de icon}}</ref>
However, following the [[1991 Soviet coup d'état attempt|attempted coup d'état]] in August, it was decided to seek independence.<ref>[http://www.sudd.ch/event.php?lang=en&id=uz021991 Uzkekistan, 29 December 1991: Independence] Direct Democracy {{de icon}}</ref> Independence was subsequently declared on 31 August,<ref>B.V. Rao (200) ''History Of Modern Europe (1789-1992)'' Sterling Publishers, p337</ref> and the Soviet Union ceased to exist on 26 December 1991,<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1991/12/26/world/end-of-the-soviet-union-the-soviet-state-born-of-a-dream-dies.html END OF THE SOVIET UNION; The Soviet State, Born of a Dream, Dies] The New York Times, 26 December 1991</ref> three days before the referendum.
==Results== {| class=wikitable style=text-align:right !Choice !Votes !% |- |align=left|For||9,718,155||98.3 |- |align=left|Against||172,294||1.7 |- |align=left|Invalid/blank votes||8,258||– |- |align=left|'''Total'''||'''9,898,707'''||'''100''' |- |align=left|Registered voters/turnout||10,515,066||94.1 |- |colspan=3 align=left|Source: Nohlen ''et al.'' |}
