{{Infobox organization |name = Virginia Science Festival |image = Virginia_Science_Festival_logo.jpg |image_border = |caption = |map = <!-- optional --> |msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 200px --> |malt = <!-- map alt text --> |abbreviation = VSF |motto = |formation = {{Start date and years ago|2014|10|04}} |extinction = <!-- date of extinction, optional --> |purpose = [[Science, Technology, Engineering, and Math|STEM]] outreach and education |headquarters = [[Blacksburg, Virginia]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = [[Virginia]] |membership = |language = <!-- official languages --> |leader_title = <!-- position title for the leader of the org --> |leader_name = <!-- name of leader --> |main_organ = <!-- gral. assembly, board of directors, etc --> |parent_organization = [[Virginia Tech]], [[Science Museum of Western North Carolina]] |affiliations = [[USA Science and Engineering Festival]] |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = virginiasciencefestival.org |remarks = }} The '''Virginia Science Festival''' (VSF) is a multi-week event encompassing events across 11 sites featuring many disciplines throughout [[Virginia]]. The festival was inaugurated in 2014,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://augustafreepress.com/fourth-virginia-tech-science-festival-returns-nov-4/|title=Fourth Virginia Tech Science Festival returns Nov. 4|date=2017-10-31|work=Augusta Free Press|access-date=2017-11-22|language=en-US}}</ref> and is organized by [[Virginia Tech]] and the [[Science Museum of Western Virginia]] with the goal of highlighting the educational, cultural, and economic impact of science in the state. NCSF events include hands-on activities, talks, and lab tours.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Allen|first1=Mark|title=Blacksburg and Roanoke kick off statewide Virginia Science Festival|url=http://www.wdbj7.com/news/local/28410820|accessdate=October 2, 2014}}</ref>
Participants have included [[NASA Langley]], [[Wallops Flight Center]], [[Virginia Department of Transportation]], [[American Red Cross]], [[WDBJ]], and [[Carilion Health Care]].
The festival was initially funded through a grant from the [[Science Festival Foundation]], the [[Alfred P. Sloan Foundation]], and [[Appalachian Power]].
